# Redux Toolkit Patterns

## Slice Structure
```ts
import { createSlice, PayloadAction } from '@reduxjs/toolkit';

export interface ItemState {
  items: Item[];
  isLoading: boolean;
  error: string | null;
}

const initialState: ItemState = {
  items: [],
  isLoading: false,
  error: null,
};

const itemSlice = createSlice({
  name: 'items',
  initialState,
  reducers: {
    setItems: (state, action: PayloadAction<Item[]>) => {
      state.items = action.payload;
    },
    setLoading: (state, action: PayloadAction<boolean>) => {
      state.isLoading = action.payload;
    },
    setError: (state, action: PayloadAction<string | null>) => {
      state.error = action.payload;
      state.isLoading = false;
    },
    clearItems: () => initialState,
  },
});

export const { setItems, setLoading, setError, clearItems } = itemSlice.actions;
export const itemReducer = itemSlice.reducer;
export default itemReducer;
```

## Conventions
- State interface exported and named `{Name}State`
- Domain types (e.g. `Message`, `HobbyRecommendation`) exported from slice file
- Sync reducers only in slice files — use `PayloadAction<T>` for all
- Full reset: `clearX: () => initialState` (return fresh object)
- Guard mutations: check `includes` before `push` to avoid duplicates
- Dual export: named `{name}Reducer` AND `export default`

## Async Thunks
Defined in `store/index.ts`, not in individual slice files:
```ts
export const fetchHobbies = createAsyncThunk(
  'hobbies/fetchHobbies',
  async (_, { rejectWithValue }) => {
    try {
      const response = await axios.get('/api/hobbies');
      return response.data.data || response.data;
    } catch (error: unknown) {
      const err = error as { response?: { data?: { message?: string } } };
      return rejectWithValue(err.response?.data?.message || 'Failed to fetch hobbies');
    }
  }
);
```

Handle in slice via `extraReducers` builder:
- `.pending` → set loading, clear error
- `.fulfilled` → set data, clear loading
- `.rejected` → set error, clear loading

## Typed Hooks
Use typed hooks from `hooks/useAppDispatch.ts` (re-exported from `store/index.ts`):
```ts
const dispatch = useAppDispatch();
const hobbies = useAppSelector((state: RootState) => state.hobbies.hobbies);
```

## Store Keys
Current store shape:
- `user` — auth state, profile
- `hobbies` — discovery, filters, localStorage saves
- `savedHobbies` — auth-based saved hobby IDs
- `ui` — theme, sidebar
- `ai` — chat history, quiz answers, recommendations
